Date: Fri 2 Mar 2001 13:09:09 -0300
From: Pedro E. Pinate <ppinate@uole.com.ve>

Temporary Closing of Venezuela's Cattle and Beef Trade from Colombia.
-----------------------------------------------
VenezuelaÂ´s Ministry of Commerce and Production decided yesterday [1 Mar
2001 to close its frontier to cattle and beef imports from its neighbor
country Colombia, in an effort to prevent the spread of BSE (bovine
spongiform encephalopathy). For the same reason, the government of Colombia
has recently slaughtered a herd of imported cattle from Europe. There has
no official report of BSE in either Colombia or Venezuela.
--
